    "31789607": {
      "title": "The mechanism of feeding and salivation in Boophilus microplus (Canestrini, 1887)",
      "abstract": "The feeding apparatus of B. microplus is a primary tanned and secondary tanned (sclerotized) cuticular structure with segments of softer untanned cuticle. It begins as a channel between the hypostome and chelicerae and within the capitulum divides to give, ventrally the pharyngeal valve, pharynx and oesophagus and above these, the salivarium and paired salivary ducts."
